<item>
            <title>[AMQ-4719] Enable &quot;Link Stealing&quot; as an option on a Connector</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/AMQ-4719</link>
                <project id="12311210" key="AMQ">ActiveMQ Classic</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The JMS Spec states that connecting with a duplicate ClientID should throw an Exception. However, for MQTT and AMQP specs &quot;Link Stealing&quot; where the last ClientID pushes out the older connection with the same ClientID should be supported. ActiveMQ supports link stealing for connections with a duplicate ConnectionID - though the ConnectionID is not something supported by MQTT or AMQP. Make Link Stealing optional - so it can be set on by default for MQTT and AMQP TransportConnectors&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12667996">AMQ-4719</key>
            <summary>Enable &quot;Link Stealing&quot; as an option on a Connector</summary>
